22/03/2009
Meanwhile, a total of 365 candidates are running for 85 mayoral posts in the local elections. Nearly 7,000 Macedonian and about 500 foreign observers are monitoring the vote. The simultaneous polls are seen as crucial for the country's aspirations to join the EU and NATO. Authorities have tightened security but expressed concern that heavy snowfall may disrupt the election process. (MIA, Makfax, A1, Beta, Tanjug, AP, AKI, AFP - 21/03/09)
